<span id="freeTextContainer15732437004946315959">Third novel by Minette Walters. Unputdownable - I consumed it voraciously in half a day. She gets better and better with every book she writes (with the exception of the short novels she wrote later which format does her style no favours). Psychological brinkmanship without ever making the reader feel queasy. Jack is the best male character I have read in a while and certainly one of my top 3 characters for this year! There was just one moment in this novel when MW almost dropped the ball - muff</span>
  <span id="freeText15732437004946315959" style="display:none">Third novel by Minette Walters. Unputdownable - I consumed it voraciously in half a day. She gets better and better with every book she writes (with the exception of the short novels she wrote later which format does her style no favours). Psychological brinkmanship without ever making the reader feel queasy. Jack is the best male character I have read in a while and certainly one of my top 3 characters for this year! There was just one moment in this novel when MW almost dropped the ball - muffed a pass, really; if that's my only complaint then this is a brilliant book!</span>
