<div id="review_735907904" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/735907904" />
    <a title="The Cats’ Mother" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5720552-the-cats-mother"><img alt="The Cats’ Mother" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1640916118p2/5720552.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/735907904?book_show_action=true">Oct 06, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="The Cats’ Mother" class="user" itemprop="url" name="The Cats’ Mother" href="/user/show/5720552-the-cats-mother">The Cats’ Mother</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5720552-the-cats-mother?shelf=from-book-club">from-book-club</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5720552-the-cats-mother?shelf=action-or-suspense-thrillers">action-or-suspense-thrillers</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5720552-the-cats-mother?shelf=x-read-in-2013">x-read-in-2013</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer735907904" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9092887191513488661">This is about the third of hers that I&apos;ve read and I&apos;ve enjoyed all of them. She again features a GP as her heroine, who gets caught up in a murder mystery when an elderly woman is found dead in her bath wearing a medieval instrument of torture. The victim was universally disliked and had a difficult relationship with her daughter and granddaughter who are then shocked to find the will reveals she left everything to the GP. The story is revealed in layers, and entries from the victims diary goin</span>
  <span id="freeText9092887191513488661" style="display:none">This is about the third of hers that I've read and I've enjoyed all of them. She again features a GP as her heroine, who gets caught up in a murder mystery when an elderly woman is found dead in her bath wearing a medieval instrument of torture. The victim was universally disliked and had a difficult relationship with her daughter and granddaughter who are then shocked to find the will reveals she left everything to the GP. The story is revealed in layers, and entries from the victims diary going back in time show how dysfunctional the family all were. <br />It's pretty dark in places but the ending didn't disappoint. </span>
  <a data-text-id="9092887191513488661" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

