<div id="review_209195510" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/209195510" />
    <a title="Barbara" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1889660-barbara"><img alt="Barbara" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1517476727p2/1889660.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/209195510?book_show_action=true">Sep 16, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Barbara" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Barbara" href="/user/show/1889660-barbara">Barbara</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer209195510" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer357965367565946377"><br/>This is a mystery more complex, clever and ambivalent than I remembered it to be from my previous reading when it first came out. Minette Walters created one of her monsters in the victim and revealed her to us bit by teasing bit. The usual humane approach and appealing characters provide balance and welcome relief. I loved every paragraph of it.<br/></span>

          </span>
        </div>


