        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1153163920" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14135035591190717785">I read this book in high school, and used it for an English book report. The story has always stayed with me; for me it is a classic, one of the first &quot;who dunnits&quot; I ever read and loved. The use of the scold&apos;s bridle in the suicide/murder is just so wonderfully original and the author had me guessing at the culprit until the very end. Highly recommend.</span>
  <span id="freeText14135035591190717785" style="display:none">I read this book in high school, and used it for an English book report. The story has always stayed with me; for me it is a classic, one of the first "who dunnits" I ever read and loved. The use of the scold's bridle in the suicide/murder is just so wonderfully original and the author had me guessing at the culprit until the very end. Highly recommend.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14135035591190717785" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
